AB  - This paper argues that the true magnitude of voluntary holdings of money balances is actuallysmaller than the magnitude of conventional M1. Preliminary calculations suggest that the discrepancy is quite substantial. These findings force us to doubt the overall validity of traditional money demand studies that employ M1 data for empirical testing.
