AB  - This comment challenges Niehans' contention that in a world of zero asset conversion costs the monetary base would disappear. It argues that a demand for standby liquidity is critical to a private financial system that is exposed to periodic stresses. The comment also takes issue with Niehans' argument that money is non-neutral by asserting the Ricardian view that government bonds are not wealth.
