SN  - 0378-4266
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/S0378-4266(86)80007-3
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0378426686800073
AB  - This paper provides an explanation for the typical and often overlooked occurrence ofundersubscribed rights offerings. We argue that due to subscription costs it may be incorrect to presume that rights offerings will be fully subscribed simply because the subscription price is set below market. We present ordinary least squares estimates and Tobit estimates which support our subscription cost rationale.
ER  - 
